investment hightlights

AUSTRALIA’S BEST PERFORMING CBD OFFICE MARKET

Underpinned by a robust New South Wales economy, demand for Sydney CBD office space has reached unprecedented levels due to a tight vacancy rate, stock withdrawals for residential conversion and a lack of new supply.

REVERSIONARY UPLIFT

The key drivers of Sydney’s forecast rental growth include constrained office supply and stock withdrawals for infrastructure, residential and hotel conversion. 179 Hyde offers an opportunity to take advantage of the current favourable leasing conditions.

OUTSTANDING INVESTMENT OPPORTUNITY

The asset offers a multi-tenanted, modern A-grade office building, underpinned by a strong income stream with a WALE of 3.9 years and is 99% occupied. Additionally, the property includes parking for 116 car spaces which is one of the highest car parking ratios in the CBD (being 1:142sqm).

PRESTIGIOUS LOCATION

Situated within the prestigious Hyde Park precinct, the property benefits from the surrounding connectivity to business hubs, culture, retail and transport options, including the new Pitt Street Metro Station and light rail. The proximity to the NSW courts and breathtaking views over Hyde Park and Sydney Harbour is an ideal choice for any occupier. This is further evidenced by the high level of tenant retention within the building.

FUTURE DEVELOPMENT POTENTIAL

Subject to relevant approvals, 179 Hyde presents a rare opportunity for a mixed use redevelopment in one of Sydney’s most desirable locations. Given its position, outlook and surrounding amenity, 179 Hyde is ideally suited for future redevelopment.

COMPELLING VALUE ON A GLOBAL SCALE

In comparison to other global gateway cities, prime property yields achieved in Sydney remain attractive with around a 2.00% to 2.25% spread against major markets such as Hong Kong, Singapore, London, New York and Tokyo (source: Savills Research).

Sydney’s ﬁnest dining establishments are sprinkled throughout the surrounding streets, including an endless choice of options for all tastes. Many of the city’s renowned cultural institutions and attractions are all within walking distance, including art galleries, museums, the Sydney Opera House and the Harbour.

At the doorstep of 179 Hyde is Hyde Park, one of Sydney CBD’s most beautiful public spaces. Occupiers of the property enjoy a rare front row seat immersed in the views over Hyde Park’s green canopy and ground plane.

the
future

179 Hyde offers future conversion potential to take advantage of the property's prime position and unrivalled views over Hyde Park and Sydney harbour that will never be built out

The opportunity remains to develop a world-class mixed use project of a quality unrivalled in Sydney’s CBD. Award winning architects SJB have prepared a comprehensive design package of two concepts being:

  • Hotel and luxury residential apartment conversion*
  • A mixed use development converting the upper levels to luxury residential apartments*
